com.softwareag.security.jaas.principals

Class AbstractSagPrincipal

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.softwareag.security.jaas.principals.AbstractSagPrincipal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SagUserPrincipal

    public abstract class AbstractSagPrincipal
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The base class for all the principal's implementations. Should be extended by every new implementation. This class implements SagPrincipal and Serializable.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        public void setName(java.lang.String aName)
        Sets the name of the principal. The name can only be set once. If you attempt to set it again, you will receive an IllegalArgumentException. The name can contain the domain name in the domain\name format, but the recommended practice is to use setDomain().
        Parameters:
        aName - The name of the principal.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If you try to overwrite the name.
